					   <strong>End global warming:</strong>
					Solar energy plays a vital role in the fight against global warming. It significantly reduces carbon emissions by reducing the use of fossil fuels. Because solar energy is a renewable and clean source, it does not emit greenhouse gases or damage the atmosphere. This reduces the impact of rising global average temperatures. Furthermore, solar energy provides a sustainable and infinite source of energy production, leading to an energy transition that leaves no harmful substances in the environment. This makes solar energy an important solution in the fight against climate change.

